## Part 2 вЂ” Business Insights

### рџ’° Insight 1: The Business Tripled in Size Overnight вЂ” July 2016

The single most important event in the dataset is a dramatic inflection in July 2016.

| Period | Orders/month | Units/month | Revenue/month |
|--------|-------------|-------------|---------------|
| JanвЂ“Jun 2016 | ~284 | ~284 | ~$492K |
| **Jul 2016** | **506** | **1,954** | **$815K** |
| AugвЂ“Dec 2016 | ~1,697 | ~6,514 | ~$1,111K |
| JanвЂ“Jun 2017 | ~1,973 | ~7,552 | ~$1,531K |

Orders grew **5Г—** and units per order jumped from 1 to ~4 in a single month. This is when Accessories and Clothing began selling alongside Bikes вЂ” expanding the average basket from a single high-value item to multiple products per order.

**Business implication:** Any analysis that uses a full-period average (e.g. "avg order value = $990") is a blend of two very different business phases. Pre-July 2016 and post-July 2016 should be treated as separate periods for trend analysis.

