## Part 3 вЂ” Business Glossary

### A

**Annual Income**
A customer's self-reported or system-recorded yearly earnings. Stored in source as a formatted varchar (`"$60,000 "`). Cleaned and cast to `DECIMAL(18,2)` in `stg_customer`. Used for customer segmentation and purchasing power analysis. 16 distinct income bands ranging from $10,000 to $170,000.

**Avg Customer LTV (Average Customer Lifetime Value)**
The estimated total revenue a customer will generate over their lifetime relationship with Adventure Works. In `fct_kpi_master`, reported as **$1,904.41**. Applies a forward-looking multiplier on top of `avg_revenue_per_customer` ($1,430.56). The exact formula is undocumented in the current model вЂ” the 33% uplift likely accounts for projected repeat purchase cycles based on observed repeat rate (33.63%).

**Avg Order Value (AOV)**
Total gross revenue divided by total number of orders. `$24,914,567 / 25,164 = $990.09`. Reflects the full multi-category period (2015вЂ“2017). AOV was significantly higher in 2015 (~$2,435) when only high-priced Bikes were sold.

**Avg Revenue per Customer**
Total gross revenue divided by unique buying customers. `$24,914,567 / 17,416 = $1,430.56`. Distinct from `avg_customer_ltv` вЂ” this is purely historical, not projected. Verified to match `fct_kpi_master`.

---

### B

**Bikes**
The core product category. 97 SKUs (32 Mountain, 43 Road, 22 Touring). Price range $539вЂ“$3,578. Gross margin 38вЂ“45% вЂ” the lowest of all four categories. Sole revenue-generating category in 2015.

**Buying Customer**
A customer record in `dim_customer` who has at least one corresponding row in `fct_sales`. 17,416 out of 18,148 registered customers (95.9%) have purchased during the 2015вЂ“2017 window.

---

### C

**Calendar / Date Spine**
The `calendar` source table and `dim_date` dimension covering Jan 13, 2015 вЂ“ Jun 30, 2017 (912 days). Used to enable date-based aggregations, period comparisons, and trend analysis. `dim_date` enriches the raw date with: `year`, `month_number`, `month_name`, `quarter`, `week_of_year`, `day_of_week`, `day_name`, `is_weekend`.

**Customer Key (`customer_key`)**
The natural integer primary key for a customer record, sourced from `customerkey` in the raw `customers` table. Range: 11,000вЂ“29,483. Used as the FK in `fct_sales`. Note: Unlike the BrazilianECommerce dataset, this is a stable customer-level key вЂ” not an order-scoped ID.

**Customer Unique ID**
Not applicable in AWDB (applies to BrazilianECommerce). In AWDB, `customer_key` is a true customer identifier.

---

### D

**Date Key (`date_key` / `order_date_key` / `return_date_key`)**
An integer surrogate key in `YYYYMMDD` format (e.g. `20160715`). Used in `fct_sales` and `fct_returns` as the join key to `dim_date`. Enables efficient date-based filtering in BI tools without string parsing.

---

### E

**Education Level**
A customer demographic attribute with 5 values: `Partial High School`, `High School`, `Partial College`, `Bachelors`, `Graduate Degree`. Counterintuitively, lower education levels correlate with higher purchase conversion rates among Professional-occupation customers.

---

### F

**Freight Value**
Not applicable in AWDB. Applies to BrazilianECommerce `order_items` table.

---

### G

**Gross Margin %**
`(Gross Revenue в€’ COGS) / Gross Revenue Г— 100`. Blended across all products and years: **41.97%**. Category breakdown:
- Accessories: 58вЂ“64%
- Clothing: 28вЂ“63%
- Components: 40вЂ“56%
- Bikes: 38вЂ“45%

**Gross Profit**
`Total Gross Revenue в€’ Total COGS = $24,914,567 в€’ $14,456,986 = $10,457,581`. Pre-calculated in `fct_kpi_master` and at line level in `fct_sales` as `order_line_profit`.

---

### H

**Homeowner**
Boolean customer attribute indicating property ownership. Source stores as `'Y'`/`'N'`; cleaned to `1`/`0` in `stg_customer` as `is_home_owner`. Homeowners earn ~$5K more annually than non-homeowners across equivalent family size brackets.

---

### I

**Income Band**
One of 16 discrete annual income groups ranging from `$10,000` to `$170,000`. Note: no `$140,000` band exists in the data. Peak concentration at `$60,000` (16.9% of customers).

**is_home_owner**
Cleaned boolean flag in `stg_customer` and `dim_customer`. `1` = homeowner, `0` = renter. Derived from raw `homeowner = 'Y'/'N'`.

**is_weekend**
Derived boolean in `dim_date`. `1` if `day_of_week IN (1, 7)` (Sunday/Saturday), else `0`. Enables weekday vs weekend sales analysis.

---

### L

**Line Item**
A single row in `fct_sales` representing one product sold within one order. Natural key: `order_number + order_line_item`. In 2015, all orders had exactly 1 line item. Post-July 2016, orders average 3.35 line items as multi-product baskets became common.

---

### M

**Marital Status**
Customer demographic with two values: `Married` / `Single`. Source stores as `'M'`/`'S'`; expanded in `stg_customer`. Roughly even split across the customer base.

**Model Name**
A product grouping above individual SKUs. For example, `"Road-150"` groups 5 size variants (44, 48, 52, 56, 62) under one model. Used in `dim_product.model_name`.

---

### O

**Occupation**
Customer demographic with 5 values: `Professional`, `Management`, `Skilled Manual`, `Clerical`, `Manual`. The Professional + Management segments represent the highest-income customers but not necessarily the highest purchase-conversion rate.

**One-Time Customer**
A customer who has placed exactly 1 order in the data window. `11,559` one-time customers (66.4% of buying customers). Key re-engagement target for second-purchase campaigns.

**Order Date Key**
Integer surrogate `YYYYMMDD` in `fct_sales`. Joins to `dim_date.date_key` for time-intelligence calculations.

**Order Line Item**
Sequential integer identifying the position of a product within an order (1, 2, 3вЂ¦). Forms composite PK with `order_number` in `fct_sales`.

**Order Line Profit**
`order_line_revenue в€’ order_line_cost`. Pre-calculated measure in `fct_sales`. Positive for all records (no loss-making lines in the dataset).

**Order Line Revenue**
`order_quantity Г— product_price`. Pre-calculated measure in `fct_sales`.

**Order Number**
Alphanumeric order identifier (e.g. `SO45080`). Natural key prefix `SO` = Sales Order. Unique per order, shared across multiple line items.

---

### P

**Product Category**
The top level of the product hierarchy. Four categories: `Bikes`, `Components`, `Clothing`, `Accessories`. Denormalised into `dim_product.product_category`.

**Product Cost**
Manufacturing or acquisition cost per unit. Sourced from `products.productcost` (`DECIMAL(18,2)`). Used to calculate COGS and margin. Joined from `dim_product` into `fct_sales` at mart build time.

**Product Key (`product_key`)**
Natural integer PK for a product. Sourced from `products.productkey`. FK in `fct_sales` and `fct_returns`.

**Product Price**
Retail selling price per unit. Sourced from `products.productprice` (`DECIMAL(18,2)`). Joined from `dim_product` into `fct_sales` and `fct_returns` at mart build time. Range: $2.29 (bottles) to $3,578.27 (Road-150 Red).

**Product Size**
Physical size attribute. Meaningful values: `S`, `M`, `L`, `XL` (clothing), numeric sizes `44`вЂ“`62` (frames/bikes). Source stores `'0'` as N/A sentinel вЂ” cleaned to `NULL` in `stg_product` via `NULLIF`.

**Product SKU**
Stock Keeping Unit. Alphanumeric product code (e.g. `HL-U509-R`). Unique per product variant. Stored in `dim_product.product_sku`.

**Product Style**
Style attribute. Meaningful value: `'U'` = Unisex. Source stores `'0'` as N/A sentinel вЂ” cleaned to `NULL` in `stg_product`.

**Product Subcategory**
Mid-level product hierarchy below Category. 37 subcategories (e.g. `Mountain Bikes`, `Helmets`, `Socks`). Denormalised into `dim_product.product_subcategory`.

**Profit Margin %**
`order_line_profit / order_line_revenue Г— 100`. Pre-calculated at line level in `fct_sales`. Blended across all products and periods: **41.97%**.

---

### R

**Repeat Customer**
A customer who has placed 2 or more distinct orders. `5,857` repeat customers (33.63% of all buyers). Once a customer repeats, they average **4.30 orders** вЂ” significantly above the overall average of 1.44.

**Repeat Customer Rate %**
`repeat_customers / total_unique_customers Г— 100 = 5,857 / 17,416 = 33.63%`. Calculated in `fct_kpi_master`.

**Return Date Key**
Integer surrogate `YYYYMMDD` in `fct_returns`. Joins to `dim_date.date_key`.

**Return Rate %**
`total_units_returned / total_units_sold Г— 100 = 1,828 / 84,174 = 2.17%`. A low rate indicating good product-market fit and quality. Calculated in `fct_kpi_master`.

**Return Value**
`return_quantity Г— product_price`. Pre-calculated in `fct_returns`. Total return value across the dataset: **$765,277.54**.

---

### S

**Sales Order (SO)**
An Adventure Works sales transaction. Identified by `order_number` (prefix `SO`). Can contain multiple line items. Each line item = one product + quantity.

**Stock Date**
The date a product was stocked or made available. Stored in source as `varchar` with mixed formats. Values are from 2001вЂ“2002 вЂ” representing product launch dates, not order-related dates. Cleaned in `stg_sales` via `COALESCE(TRY_CONVERT 23, 101)`.

**Surrogate Key**
A system-generated integer key with no business meaning, used to uniquely identify rows in a dimension table. `fct_returns.return_id` is a surrogate key (`BIGINT`). `dim_date.date_key` is a surrogate key (`INT YYYYMMDD`). `dim_customer` does not currently use a surrogate key вЂ” uses the natural `customer_key` from source.

---

### T

**Territory**
A geographic sales region. 10 territories across 3 continents. Key: `territory_key` (formerly `salesterritorykey`). Hierarchy: `territory в†’ country в†’ continent`. Australia is the top-revenue territory.

**Territory Key (`territory_key`)**
Natural integer PK for a sales territory (1вЂ“10). FK in `fct_sales` and `fct_returns`.

**Total Children**
Number of dependants reported for a customer. Integer, range 0вЂ“5. Positively correlated with income вЂ” customers with 5 children average $72,760 annual income vs $54,160 for childless customers.

**Total COGS**
`SUM(order_line_cost)` across all transactions. `$14,456,986.32` for 2015вЂ“2017. Used with `total_gross_revenue` to derive `total_gross_profit` and `gross_margin_pct`.

---

### U

**Units Sold**
`SUM(order_quantity)` across all line items. **84,174 units** across 2015вЂ“2017. Distinct from number of orders (25,164) and line items (56,046) вЂ” a single line item can have `order_quantity > 1`.

---

### W

**Weekend Flag (`is_weekend`)**
`1` if the date falls on a Saturday or Sunday, `0` otherwise. Derived attribute in `dim_date`. Enables weekday/weekend sales pattern analysis.
